                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/6952.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">Winslow</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Flagship “San Diego</hi>,” <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Francisco</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>M–3109. <hi rend="italic">Annapolis</hi> from Topolobampo reports: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Absolutely nothing has been done by Mexico for relief of Americans here.
                            A band of about 30 Villa forces was in outskirts of Los Mochis today
                            driving off stock belonging to Americans. Colonel Escobar, before
                            retiring to San Bias, last night without permission entered warehouse of
                            United Sugar Companies and removed therefrom a large quantity of corn
                            and beans. It is hard to say which are the worst, the Indians or
                            Carranza forces.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winslow.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
